cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image captioning. It also involves natural language processing, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of attention mechanisms and the encoder-decoder framework suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the merging of visual and semantic information suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the evaluation of the proposed approach on benchmark datasets suggests that it could also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
